		Steps to reproduce: Open ShowsActivity rotate device select e.g.: Favorites in dropdownmenu The problem is that the field mFragment is not set if savedInstanceState is not null (e.g.: after rotating the device). To solve this problem, you can set the field mFragment, on every time the ShowsFragment is attached to the FragmentActivity by override onAttachFragment in ShowsActivity @Override
public void onAttachFragment (Fragment fragment) {
    if(fragment instanceof ShowsFragment){
        mFragment=fragment;
    }
} or add another elseif clause in the onCreate regards, David

		the dividers in the drawermenu are selectable. Just implement this in the BaseNavDrawerActivity.DrawerAdapter public boolean areAllItemsEnabled() {
    return false;
}

public boolean isEnabled(int position) {
    return getItemViewType(position) != VIEW_TYPE_DIVIDER;
} regards, David

		It's possible for the FAB to be displayed on the "now" tab as a result of the FabAbsListViewScrollDetector getting confused about which Fragment is currently being shown. Personally, I don't like hiding the FAB, but I'm not sure how you'd like to handle it. An easy fix would be just to check to see if the grid has focus or not:     if (!view.hasFocus() || totalItemCount == 0) {
        return;
    }
